Global External Beam Radiotherapy Market Insights
External Beam Radiotherapy Market size was valued at USD 4.9 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 7.7 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 6.0% from 2024 to 2030.

External Beam Radiotherapy Market Overview
The external beam radiotherapy market is projected to reach a value of USD 7.02 billion by 2028, growing at a CAGR of 5.5% from 2023 to 2028. This growth is driven by technological advancements in radiotherapy equipment and an increasing demand for cancer treatment globally. External beam radiotherapy is a critical treatment option for a variety of cancers, delivering targeted radiation from outside the body. The rise in cancer cases, an aging population, and innovations such as proton therapy and image-guided radiotherapy (IGRT) are key factors influencing the market growth. Additionally, healthcare infrastructure expansion in emerging markets is expected to further support the adoption of advanced external beam radiotherapy solutions.

